centers, 5G, IoT infrastructure, smart city projects) divided by the total
words in the report. This yields a percentage indicating the emphasis on
digital infrastructure in the region’s policy agenda. A higher INF suggests
the region has more developed digital infrastructure and focus,
which likely benefits firms implementing AI.
Control Variables: We incorporate a set of control variables that
might also influence corporate financialization, based on prior literature.
All controls are from the same financial dataset and are defined as
follows. Return on Equity (ROE), measured as net profit divided by the
average shareholders’ equity, controls for profitability from the owners’
perspective (distinct from the profit margin mediator). Higher ROE
could either reduce financialization (if profits are reinvested or paid out)
or increase it (if retained as cash). Current Ratio (Liquid) is the ratio of
current assets to current liabilities, included to control for liquidity
needs and working capital management. Firms with higher liquidity
may hold more financial current assets. Financial Leverage (FL) is
calculated as EBIT
EBT where EBIT is earnings before interest and taxes (net
profit +interest +taxes) and EBT is earnings before taxes (net profit +
taxes). This ratio essentially captures the impact of interest expenses on
earnings; a higher value indicates higher leverage (if interest is significant,
EBIT/EBT >1). We control for FL because leverage can affect both
the ability to invest in AI and the need to hold financial assets (highly
leveraged firms might hold more cash as a buffer, or less if creditors
impose restrictions). Board Independence (Indep) is measured as the
number of independent directors divided by the total number of directors
on the board. We include this to account for corporate governance
quality, as boards with greater independence may exercise more
prudent financial oversight, potentially affecting financial asset policies.
Finally, Institutional Ownership (INST) is the proportion of shares held
by institutional investors. Higher institutional ownership could pressure
management either to deploy cash efficiently (reducing idle financial
asset holdings) or could tolerate financial investments if seen as prudent.
These control variables are included as standard determinants to isolate
the effect of AI and ensure our results are not confounded by these
factors. All variables with their descriptions, abbreviations, and data
