These results provide strong support for Hypothesis 2: AI adoption increases
corporate financialization partly by enhancing firm profitability,
which generates surplus funds that are subsequently allocated to
financial assets. However, the substantial remaining direct effect indicates
that profitability is only one of multiple pathways through which
AI influences financial asset holdings. In economic interpretation, AI-
