signals to investors and lenders that the firm is innovative and forward-
looking, enhancing its reputation and creditworthiness. Second, AI
implementation often improves operational performance and reduces
earnings volatility, making firms less risky in creditors’ assessments.
Third, in the Chinese institutional context, government policies
increasingly favor technology-oriented firms with preferential financing
access and subsidies. Fourth, successful AI deployment generates valuable
intangible assets including data capabilities and algorithmic know-
how that, while difficult to collateralize directly, strengthen the firm’s
overall competitive position and future cash flow prospects, thereby
improving financing terms.
