adoption as a pure cost or speculative investment, investors should
recognize that AI can materially affect firms’ financial asset positions
and overall financial health through profitability improvements and
financing constraint alleviation. When assessing firms’ AI strategies,
investors should examine not just the technology investments themselves
but also the complementary capabilities and contextual factors
determining likely success. Firms with strong digital foundations, technologically
sophisticated management, and operations in digitally
advanced regions merit higher valuations for AI initiatives due to
greater probability of successful implementation and financial value
